WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.639 --> 00:00:08.800
Hello, thank you for clicking on my video.

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:11.800
This is a special program for "Ryuichi Sakamoto BTTB Box Set."

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:16.039
It's a pure unboxing video without any background music.

00:00:16.039 --> 00:00:19.039
The content is divided into three parts.

00:00:19.039 --> 00:00:23.400
A 5-minute immersive unboxing + page-by-page sheet music browsing, and an 8-minute CD listening session.

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:28.519
For more details about the album purchase and introduction, please refer to the main program on this channel.

00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:41.119
When recording this, it was my first time opening this box set.

00:00:41.119 --> 00:00:47.599
I spent a long time figuring out what all these papers and clippings were.

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:09.800
Later, I looked it up and found out that Miu Sakamoto is Ryuichi Sakamoto's daughter.

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:16.280
I spent more time identifying them and realized the back had nothing to do with Ryuichi Sakamoto (facepalm).

00:01:38.719 --> 00:01:45.199
It was hard to believe that these were magazine clippings from 1999.

00:01:45.199 --> 00:01:51.679
I wondered at the time if this was the "Contemporary Music Magazine" of that era.

00:01:51.679 --> 00:01:58.159
They were preserved in the box like they were brand new.

00:02:36.719 --> 00:02:43.199
When opening it for the first time, the tape was still intact.

00:02:44.480 --> 00:02:50.960
Sorry, the text here is too small, making it especially hard to focus.

00:03:23.119 --> 00:03:29.599
I was so afraid of damaging it at the time that I didn’t even dare to breathe.

00:03:41.840 --> 00:03:47.800
Finally, after finishing the unboxing, I took a deep breath.

00:03:49.679 --> 00:03:55.639
I recently bought a new reading stand, perfect for flipping through sheet music.

00:03:55.639 --> 00:04:01.599
It’s a cheap one from Amazon Canada that frees up your hands while reading.

00:04:04.320 --> 00:04:08.159
I can't help but share a little more with everyone.

00:04:08.159 --> 00:04:12.000
Last November, at the Royal Conservatory of Music in Toronto,

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.360
I attended a performance by Barbara Hannigan &amp; Bertrand Chamayou.

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:20.400
During the last piece, Barbara had to sing and flip through sheet music simultaneously.

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:24.719
The card sheets were about this size.

00:04:24.719 --> 00:04:29.039
Her live performance was incredibly passionate.

00:04:29.039 --> 00:04:33.360
I was so worried she might flip too many or too few pages and affect her singing.

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:37.679
While browsing Ryuichi Sakamoto's sheet music this time,

00:04:37.679 --> 00:04:42.000
I realized that these professional card sheets are particularly sturdy.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:46.320
They’re easy to flip and hard to turn multiple pages by accident. They feel great to handle.

00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:52.320
Alright, there are almost no subtitles left (CD listening starts at 8:19).

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:27.800
Inspired by the previous collector,

00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:31.440
I decided to put the poster I brought back from Tokyo,

00:07:31.440 --> 00:07:35.760
the 2023 "Ryuichi Sakamoto OPUS" movie version, into the box.

00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:40.079
It’ll be my addition to this collection.

00:07:40.079 --> 00:07:44.400
Due to its size, it couldn’t fit in the box, so I had to leave it outside.

00:08:33.560 --> 00:08:40.279
This MUJI CD player was turned up to maximum volume. Be aware the speakers will distort.

00:08:40.279 --> 00:08:40.920
4

00:08:40.920 --> 00:08:41.560
3

00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:42.199
2

00:08:42.199 --> 00:08:42.840
Beep.

00:14:27.399 --> 00:14:38.600
It sounds so good, I can’t bring myself to pause it.

00:14:38.600 --> 00:14:45.319
I reluctantly rewound it to the first track.

00:14:45.319 --> 00:14:58.159
That concludes the behind-the-scenes of the "Ryuichi Sakamoto BTTB Unboxing."

00:14:58.159 --> 00:15:08.760
Your support is my greatest motivation to create more. See you next time!

